external.description: Internet trolls are people who deliberately post provocative, inflammatory, rude, or off-topic comments online with the main goal of upsetting others, starting arguments, or getting strong emotional reactions.  The term comes from "trolling" (like fishing — dropping bait and waiting for a bite), and it has been around since the early days of the internet (Usenet in the 1990s), but exploded with social media.  Here are some classic examples of the Troll Face meme, the iconic symbol of internet trolling:  And here's the "angry keyboard warrior" vibe that many trolls embody — raging from behind a screen:  Common Characteristics of Internet Trolls Anonymity — They usually hide behind throwaway accounts, no profile picture, or obvious fake names. Provocation for fun — They often don't care about the actual topic; they just want chaos, attention, or laughs (at others' expense). Lack of empathy — Many studies link heavy trolling to dark personality traits (the so-called Dark Tetrad): high levels of sadism (enjoying others' suffering), psychopathy, Machiavellianism, and sometimes narcissism. Disinhibition — People say/do things online they'd never do face-to-face because of anonymity + physical distance ("online disinhibition effect"). Motivations vary: boredom, revenge, power trip, political/ideological agenda, schadenfreude (pleasure at others' misfortune), or even low self-esteem + high FOMO leading to seeking attention.  Types of Trolls (a non-complete list) Classic baiter — Posts obvious nonsense to see who falls for it ("all people who like pineapple on pizza should be deported") Rage inducer — Goes for personal insults, especially on sensitive topics Concern troll — Pretends to be on your side while sowing doubt ("I'm a lifelong fan but...") Shock troll — Posts extremely offensive content just to disgust people Political/agenda troll — Pushes propaganda, often in coordinated groups (troll farms) RIP troll — The worst kind — posts vile comments on memorial pages  In short:   An internet troll is basically someone who treats other humans online like NPCs in a video game — poke them until they react, then laugh at the explosion.  The vast majority of us just want normal conversations. Trolls want to watch the world burn... one comment section at a time. 😈
